| GRTS Cell Id: | GRTS ID number of the NABat grid cell where the survey was conducted. This is also the NABat sampling priority of the grid cell based on the GRTS master sample; for example; lower GRTS ID = higher NABat sampling priority.
SITE_ID: A concatenation of the LAT, LONG, and YEAR. Data is summarized based upon this field.
SPARCS: Acronym for Species, Age, Reproductive Condition, and Sex.
BAT_ID: Typically the bat species, combined with the band number or radio frequency, project name. Used for connecting captured bats with roost trees.
NET_HT: Capture height in net in meters
SAMPLE: Type of samples taken (e.g., wing punch, gua, hair).
BAND: Whether the bat is newly banded or a recapture
BAND_COLOR: Band color (e.g., silver metal, purple plastic, etc.).
BAND_ID: Concatenation of the species code, band color, and band number.
BAND_ARM: Which wing the band was applied
SITE: The name of the location, site, and date the bat was captured
ACCURACY: General description of the accuracy of the GPS coordinates. Drop down categories.
DATE: Contatenation of the previous 3. Formatting was done this way because Excel can format dates in multiple different ways.
START_TIME: Start time for the survey night
STOP_TIME: Stop time for the survey night
STATE: State the survey site occurs within
COUNTY: County the survey site occurs within (this is used to verify the accuracy of the GPS coordinates).
TYPE: Type of survey that was conducted (e.g., summer mist-net, fall harp trap, other).
EFFORT: The number of net or trap sets used on the survey night.
EFFORT_HRS: Number of nets/traps * the number of survey hours
STATUS: Number of days since the survey was conducted. Used to determine whether the results of a negative survey are still current or expired.
FILE_NAME: Name of the excel file the surveyor submitted to the database.
